featured_reviews.review_id: A great place for peace in mind. Millions of people were praying, but everything was neat and clean. The modern architecture was worth viewing. The tombs of the masjid opens up and fresh air fills up the inside.  These are beautiful sights. The prayers are so soothing and one can concentrate peacefully inside the masjid for hours together. Fazil ashab jumma Masjid  is the perfect place for those who need to pray peacefully for long time.

featured_reviews.review_id: The imam lives nearby. The upper floor of the mosque is for ladies. It is little to the interior if you are coming from ECR road. Its far from OMR road. If you are living in Arihant Escapade, there is a shortcut to go to this mosque (only by foot, cycle or two wheeler as the lane is to narrow and is flooded during rainy season). if you are coming back from the mosque, once you cross the bridge of black watter nalla, take a left and then first right, walk couple of meters and then take a left then keep your eyes open for a narrow passage to your right, (the passage in not more than 4 feet wide but has lap posts on it) once the passage ends you will reach near the back end of the small society at the back side of Arihant.
